using Xunit.Sdk;
using Xunit.v3;

namespace MyApp.Tests;

public class AlphabeticalOrderer : ITestCaseOrderer
{
    public IReadOnlyCollection<TTestCase> OrderTestCases<TTestCase>(
        IReadOnlyCollection<TTestCase> testCases) where TTestCase : ITestCase
    {
        return testCases.OrderBy(tc => tc.TestCaseDisplayName, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase).ToList();
    }
}

data.reasoningText:
Now I have the full picture. The `ITestCaseOrderer` interface in xUnit.net v3 is:

```csharp
namespace Xunit.v3
{
    public interface ITestCaseOrderer
    {
        IReadOnlyCollection<TTestCase> OrderTestCases<TTestCase>(IReadOnlyCollection<TTestCase> testCases) where TTestCase : ITestCase;
    }
}
```

Where `ITestCase` is in the `Xunit.Sdk` namespace.

Now, from the migration docs I read earlier, test cases have `TestCaseDisplayName` property in v3 (was `DisplayName` in v2).


I'll implement the `AlphabeticalOrderer` class that implements this interface to sort test cases alphabetically by their display names.

